Easy to Install
===============
In WordPress, with the plugin: It includes a WordPress plugin that You just need to activate. Then You will have the widget available for You to add on Your site.

In plain HTML, with jQuery: Just add as many RSSWidgets as You want in your HTML, with $('#element').rssWidget({...});

Highly Configurable
===================
You can modify: 
-the format of the dates (including the name of the months)
-the HTML structure of the feed items that are shown
-the styles, via the (highly commented) CSS file
-You can install as many RSSWidgets as You want into the same site
-the maximum number of news items to show on each feed

Compatible
==========
Tested in Internet Explorer 6,7,8, Firefox 2,3 (Mac & PC), Safari, Chrome and Opera.

